			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">As long as we continue to be outpaced by true DPS classes, I think charm is relatively safe.  As you said, we finally reached the DPS of Tipt pets again.  Well, guess what, true DPS classes are no longer doing the same DPS they were in GoD.  Back then, our charm pet DPS beat a whole group.  Now, true DPS classes can break 3k DPS.  So, we are not quite as good as a wizard (strictly in terms of DPS), but our DPS is a lot riskier.
<br />

<br />
Oh, and just because we can take a round of attacks from an ex-pet a little better than we could back then (which is only really true if your gear level is sufficient for the charmed pet we are using), does not mean that there is no risk of death on a charm break anymore.  Those who still approach charm from the standpoint of &quot;don't get hit&quot; are far more successful (not to mention efficient) with charm than those who get sloppy.  And, with aggro on the charmed pet after break being less guaranteed now than back then, the risk to others is slightly higher now than it was back then.
<br />

<br />
Mori</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
