			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The way I understand the  mob changes are:
<br />

<br />
-Mobs traditionally had low attack, and enormous max hits accounted for dps increases.
<br />

<br />
-SoF mobs have reduced the % increase in max hit in exchange for a large increase in attack, and a large increase of the benefits of statistics for the mobs.
<br />

<br />
The net result is that you have an expansion where the max hits dont mudflate as much as they have in the past BUT the mobs are still very tough to tank. AC becomes even more important. Also stat debuffs such as cripple now provide meaningful DPS reduction.
<br />

<br />
What this means for our charmed pets is basically more max hits, a lot more. 
<br />

<br />
In theory it also makes mage pet armor more valuable because presumably now a lvl 79 warrior mob with armor has roughly equivalent defense as a PC lvl 80 warior in the same gear. The mobs advantage is that it has a vast HP resource.
<br />

<br />
Break Down:
<br />
PC = High AC, low hps
<br />
NPC = Low AC, high HPs (and now high attack)
<br />

<br />
Honestly I think the reason they are changing it like this is to give themselves more control over mob dps. Meaning they can provide us with more customized mobs. 
<br />

<br />
For instance they could have a theme where orcs in a certain zone had lower max hit but high attack, but some giants in the same zone could have high max hit and low attack. Yet others could have a mixture of the styles. 
<br />

<br />
The more variables they add to the mobs the better imo, it gives us new weaknesses to exploit.<br />_________________<br />&quot;Those who stand with me shall be my brothers.&quot; -Vizier
<br />
<a href="http://reborninfire.org" target="_blank">http://reborninfire.org</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
