				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Mobs where hitting on an <span style="font-weight: bold">average</span> of DI:15 before.  There is only so much room to go up in ATK.  All DI:20 is only a 15% to 20% boost in average hit damage, because DB applies regardless.
<br />

<br />
What can give more than a 20% boost would be higher DW chances (however, that was already at 80% -- so only room for another +11% DPS).  
<br />

<br />
A lower delay also boosts the DPS:max hit ratio.  Note that the trained griffons in Direwind has a VERY short delay compared to other mobs.
<br />

<br />
A better double attack could boost DPS.  Lemme work out what their old double attack was -- I think it was pretty damn good...
<br />

<br />
Lastly, a higher ACCURACY could boost mob DPS massively, by a good +50% or more.
<br />

<br />
But good old ATK power can't make that much difference.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
